{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/17597", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/17597/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/17597/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/17597/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/17597", "id": 44193485, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0NDE5MzQ4NQ==", "number": 17597, "title": "Mutable indexing is strange.", "user": {"login": "HeroesGrave", "id": 1934172, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE5MzQxNzI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1934172?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/HeroesGrave", "html_url": "https://github.com/HeroesGrave", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HeroesGrave/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HeroesGrave/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HeroesGrave/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HeroesGrave/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HeroesGrave/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HeroesGrave/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HeroesGrave/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HeroesGrave/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/HeroesGrave/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2014-09-27T21:57:55Z", "updated_at": "2014-11-28T01:01:47Z", "closed_at": "2014-11-28T01:01:47Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Mutably indexing a `Vec` (and probably lots of other collections) is weird.\nOn one hand, you can dereference a mutable pointer:\n\n``` rust\n*vec.get_mut(index) = value;\n```\n\nWhich is ugly and inconsistent with immutable indexing (`vec[index]`)\n\nWith the new slicing syntax you can do this:\n\n``` rust\nvec[mut][index] = value;\n```\n\nWhich is arguably nicer. But wouldn't something like:\n\n``` rust\nvec[mut index] = value;\n```\n\nBe even better and more consistent?\n", "closed_by": {"login": "Gankra", "id": 1136864, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjExMzY4NjQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1136864?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Gankra", "html_url": "https://github.com/Gankra", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Gankra/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Gankra/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Gankra/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Gankra/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Gankra/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Gankra/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Gankra/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Gankra/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Gankra/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/17597/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/17597/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}